
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `autoupdate` baraye be-rooz resani khodkaar-e barname-ha va narm-afzar-ha estefade mishavad. In dastoor, barname-ha ra az tarigh internet be akharin version be-rooz mikonad.  

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `autoupdate enable`  --> ✅ Roshan kardan be-rooz resani khodkaar.  
    🔹 `autoupdate disable` --> 🚫 Kh خاموش kardan be-rooz resani khodkaar.  
    🔹 `autoupdate check`   --> 🔎 Barresi baraye be-rooz resani-haye jadid bedoon nasb.  
    🔹 `autoupdate now`     --> 🚀 Shoru-e fori be-rooz resani.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**
    
    $ autoupdate enable
    
    🔹 Roshan kardan be-rooz resani khodkaar.

    $ autoupdate check
    
    🔹 Barresi baraye be-rooz resani-haye jadid bedoon nasb.

✅ **Mesal sade:**
    
    $ autoupdate now
    
    🔹 Dastoor shoru be be-rooz resani fori mikonad agar version jadid mojud bashad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `autoupdate` command is used to automatically update programs and software. This command updates the programs to the latest version via the internet.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `autoupdate enable`  --> ✅ Enable automatic updates.
    🔹 `autoupdate disable` --> 🚫 Disable automatic updates.
    🔹 `autoupdate check`   --> 🔎 Check for new updates without installing them.
    🔹 `autoupdate now`     --> 🚀 Start the update process immediately.

🛠 **Examples:**
    
    $ autoupdate enable
    
    🔹 Enables automatic updates.

    $ autoupdate check
    
    🔹 Checks for new updates without installing them.

✅ **Simple Example:**
    
    $ autoupdate now
    
    🔹 The command starts updating immediately if a newer version is available.

